#: ../../language/error_codes/E4151.md:1
msgid "E4151"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4151.md:3
msgid ""
"Values of type `FuncRef[T]` must be closed function -- it should not "
"capture any local variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4151.md:5
msgid ""
"MoonBit provides a builtin type `FuncRef[T]`, which represents closed "
"function of type `T`. In MoonBit's native backend, `FuncRef[T]` "
"corresponds to function pointer type, so `FuncRef[T]` can be passed to C "
"FFI functions requiring a callback directly, for example setting UNIX "
"signal handler. Values of type `FuncRef[T]` must be closed function type,"
" if a function which captures free variables or a non-function is "
"supplied, an error will be reported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4151.md:11
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4151.md:12
msgid ""
"test {\n"
"  let x : Int = 42\n"
"  let _ : FuncRef[() -> Unit] = fn () { println(x) }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4151.md:16
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4151.md:17
msgid ""
"If your callback function really needs to have captures, consider adding "
"the captures as extra parameters to the function."
msgstr ""

